Writing Normalizing function and importing data from a text file.

minmax<-function(x)
{
  (x-min(x))/(max(x)-min(x))
}

Normalizing and splitting the data into 70-30 ratio for Testing and Training.

dN<-apply(data,2,minmax)
library(caTools)
Split<-sample.split(dN[,25],SplitRatio=0.7)
train<-subset(dN,Split==TRUE)
test<-subset(dN,Split==FALSE)

Plotting the Neural Network based on optimal number of Nodes. For predicting Thermal Conductivity from all other data.

Testing on Data.


output <- predict(nn,  test[,-3:-25])

Err_InternalEnergy <- mean((output[,1] - test[,5])^2)
print(paste("Mean Square Error in Internal Energy Prediction is ", Err_InternalEnergy*100))
[1] "Mean Square Error in Internal Energy Prediction is  0.15954327104741"
Err_Enthalpy <- mean((output[,2] - test[,6])^2)
print(paste("Mean Square Error in Enthalpy Prediction is ", Err_Enthalpy*100))
[1] "Mean Square Error in Enthalpy Prediction is  0.500258803960607"
Err_Entropy <- mean((output[,3] - test[,7])^2)
print(paste("Mean Square Error in Entropy Prediction is ", Err_Entropy*100))
[1] "Mean Square Error in Entropy Prediction is  2.89483939334729"
